          "prompt_html": "<h1>MULTIPLE CHOICE 07</h1><p><strong>Questions 11 - 15</strong></p><p>Choose the correct letter, <strong>A, B or C</strong>.</p><p>11 Who has organised the safety talk?</p><table><thead><tr><th><strong>A</strong>    The Students' Union</th><th></th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td><strong>B</strong>    Westley police station</td><td></td></tr><tr><td><strong>C</strong>    Staff at the University of Westley</td><td></td></tr></tbody></table><p>12 What does the policeman suggest is the reason a lot of crimes happen?</p><table><thead><tr><th><strong>A</strong>    People don't have time to learn about security</th><th></th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td><strong>B</strong>    People don't have money to improve security</td><td></td></tr><tr><td><strong>C</strong>    People don't remember basic safety rules</td><td></td></tr></tbody></table><p>13 What crime against students is the most common at university?</p><table><thead><tr><th><strong>A</strong>    Theft</th><th></th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td><strong>B</strong>    Mugging</td><td></td></tr><tr><td><strong>C</strong>    Fraud</td><td></td></tr></tbody></table><p>14 What is PC Fair's advice to avoid being a victim of theft?</p><table><thead><tr><th><strong>A</strong>    Lock doors, lock windows, keep curtains shut</th><th></th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td><strong>B</strong>    Lock doors, keep curtains shut, hide valuables</td><td></td></tr><tr><td><strong>C</strong>    Lock doors, lock windows, hide valuables</td><td></td></tr></tbody></table><p>15 What does PC Fair suggest students do to reduce the potential damage of theft for themselves?</p><table><thead><tr><th><strong>A</strong>    Insure and permanently label possessions</th><th></th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td><strong>B</strong>    Insure possessions and avoid lending them</td><td></td></tr><tr><td><strong>C</strong>    Permanently label possessions and avoid lending them</td><td></td></tr></tbody></table>",
